🧠 Why Developers Use Docker

Developers use Docker to:

✅ Ensure same runtime environment

✅ Avoid dependency conflicts

✅ Run full backend ecosystem locally

✅ Match production environment

✅ Simplify onboarding

✅ Run infrastructure services easily

🏗 Running Full Backend Ecosystem

A Spring Boot application rarely runs alone.

It may depend on:

🗄 MySQL

⚡ Redis

📨 Kafka

🔎 Elasticsearch

🔁 Other microservices

Without Docker:

Manual installation

Version mismatch

Port conflicts

Configuration issues

With Docker:

docker compose up

🔥 Entire system starts instantly.

📦 Example docker-compose.yml
version: '3'
services:
  app:
    build: .
    ports:
      - "8080:8080"

  mysql:
    image: mysql:8
    environment:
      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: root

  redis:
    image: redis

Every developer runs identical infrastructure.

