🐳 Docker Image vs Container
Image	Container
Blueprint	Running instance
Read-only	Writable layer
Stored permanently	Temporary
Versioned	Ephemeral

⚠ Containers are immutable in professional workflows.

🔁 Proper Development Workflow

If teammate wants to modify code:

Clone Git repository

Modify source code

Commit & push

Build new Docker image

Run container

docker build -t springboot-dev .
docker run -p 8080:8080 springboot-dev
🛠 What Happens During docker build
docker build -t springboot-dev .
Internally:

1️⃣ Docker reads Dockerfile
2️⃣ Pulls base image (if not present)
3️⃣ Copies project files
4️⃣ Executes build commands (e.g., Maven)
5️⃣ Creates new image

The build happens inside an isolated container environment.

No dependency conflicts.

🛠 What Happens During docker run
docker run -p 8080:8080 springboot-dev

Docker:

Creates container from image

Executes ENTRYPOINT

Starts Spring Boot app

Example:

ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","app.jar"]
🔥 Multi-Stage Build (Production Best Practice)
# Stage 1 - Build
FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests

# Stage 2 - Runtime
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jdk
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/target/app.jar app.jar
ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","app.jar"]
Benefits

Smaller image

No Maven in runtime

More secure

Optimized for production

🔒 Container Changes (Important)

Yes, you can enter a container:

docker exec -it <container_id> bash

But:

Changes are temporary

Not version-controlled

Lost when container is removed

Proper way:
Modify source code → Rebuild image → Run container.

🌿 Merge Conflicts

Merge conflicts occur in Git, not Docker.

Example:

<<<<<<< HEAD
return "Ranjeeta";
=======
return "Team Member";
>>>>>>> branch-name

Resolved manually in Git.

Docker does not handle code merging.

🧩 Dependency Conflict Clarification
If teammate pulls Docker image:
docker pull ranjeeta/springboot-app
docker run ranjeeta/springboot-app

✅ No dependency conflict
Because image already contains:

JDK

OS

Dependencies

Compiled JAR

If teammate clones Git and runs without Docker:

⚠ Conflicts possible due to:

Different JDK version

Different Maven version

Different DB version

Different OS

Docker prevents this by freezing environment.

📡 Docker Networking

In docker-compose:

Services communicate using service name:

services:
  app:
    depends_on:
      - mysql
  mysql:
    image: mysql

Inside Spring Boot:

spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://mysql:3306/db

mysql acts as hostname automatically.

💾 Data Persistence (Important)

Without volumes:

docker run mysql

Delete container → Data lost.

With volume:

docker run -v mysql_data:/var/lib/mysql mysql

Data persists even if container is removed.

🎯 Final Understanding

🐳 Docker = Immutable environment + Deployment artifact
🌿 Git = Code collaboration + Version control

Containers should be treated as immutable.
All changes must happen in source code → rebuild image → run container.

